I had an amazing time yesterday at the inaugural @sulwhasoo.us x @metmuseum party, celebrating the art, heritage, and beauty of the Korean ginseng. 

To be able to design the tasting menu and canapes for this inspirational evening alongside @olivierchengcatering production team was an inspirational journey. Celebrating the future of Korean heritage in such an amazing NYC landmark is a memory I will cherish for many years to come. Thank you!

Thank you @michelinguide for including our NARO in the most recent round-up here in New York.

Among our restaurants, @naro.nyc is most deeply rooted in traditional Korean cuisine and inspired by Korea's historic past. At NARO, we find ourselves contemplating the preservation of our culture, which we built over the years through Atoboy and Atomix. 

As Atoboy and Atomix look towards our ever-so-evolving culture, NARO is our homage to our heritage and our traditions. To showcase such a meaningful restaurant in the historic Rockefeller Center, is truly a dream-come-true.

📷 @evansungnyc @charissa_fay
@wonsoju_global celebrates its US launching party! From April 7th to 15th, @wonsoju is exclusively available in @seoulsalon.nyc 📷 @ye.fan

When embarking on a new project, we take many factors taken into consideration. There are the hospitality basics: delicious cuisine, comfortable atmosphere, and warm service. Beyond that, we always consider the impact on the community it resides in: is it positive, constructive, creative? 

If @atoboynyc and @atomixnyc were manifestations of our personal visions for ‘New Korean’ cuisine in NYC, @naro.nyc is our dedication to spreading the cuisine and culture of Hansik, traditional Korean cuisine. 

With NARO, the aspiration is to introduce a lesser known side of Korean cuisine to NYC, and hopefully the world. Unlike the widely known and beloved Korean flavors - often marked by bold, powerful and complex flavors - NARO will focus on highlighting the subtle, deceptively simple, yet deeply profound flavors that characterize the essence of Hansik’s philosophy. 

My wish is that NARO will help pioneer yet another new chapter of Korean cuisine here in New York City, to the world.

Thank you to @nytimes @nytcooking and @pete_wells for including @atomixnyc in this year's list. 
We are always humbled to be a part of the diversity of culture and cuisine in NYC, truly like no other city in the world. A special thanks to our team past and present, as well as our guests who have shown us unwavering support through the last five years. 🥹

Younglae Kim @kimyounglae_ the founder and director of @studio_writers was the first partner that came to mind when we began drawing the picture of NARO in our minds. It was a priority to work with a designer who knew of the essence and philosophy of Korea’s aesthetics, as well as a well-developed understanding of our taste. 

When we first began our shared vision for @naro.nyc one of the first conversations we had was about the desire to take a different approach than the widely-accepted aesthetics of eastern Asia. While undoubtedly beautiful and timeless, the combination of natural wood or stone materials, often described as ‘zen’, as well as the well-known Asian lounge aesthetics, marked by darker tones and moodier lighting, was not the direction we wanted to take.

With NARO, we wanted to achieve an atmosphere rooted in Korean aesthetics which expressed light, energy, and health. This was achieved by celestial aesthetics and ethereal materials. This pursuit is continued in our choice of Korean ceramics, paper goods, and curated artworks.

A big congratulations to our @naro.nyc family who has worked with big dreams, deep faith, and admirable discipline for many months, some even years.

I believe that the kind words that NARO has received will open new doors for us, and for the future of dining in NYC.

I hope we all can take a moment to take in and remember the feelings of excitement and togetherness that is gifted to us today, and to use that to fuel our future for many years to come. Like NARO's namesake, 'through us' we dream of and work towards a better, brighter future. Fighting! 💪

It is a true milestone in my career, and a deeply joyful personal moment, to officially announce my first published cookbook: The Korean Cookbook.

Stemming from a conversation before the onset of Covid, my last three years were spent with countless nights researching, writing, and editing to deliver the beauty of Korean cuisine to the world, with Seoul-based co-author, longtime peer and great friend JY Choi @choi.keats 

Pre-orders are now live through a link in bio, shipping October 2023. We are especially honored be a part of the monumental #Phaidon100 campaign, celebrating 100 amazing years of Phaidon. 

Thank you to everyone, near and far, who has made this dream possible. 

#TheKoreanCookbook

Thank you @beardfoundation for one of the biggest honor of my career. I am so excited to bring this back to our team who has joined me and Ellia on this journey, and I take this as a sign to do better, dream bigger, and work harder. 
Food is the ultimate love language and what has (and will continue to) bring all of us together. Let’s make this world a better place through food! 
#jbfa

It is a humbling, tremendous honor for @atomixnyc to rank #8 on the World 50 Best 2023. Our foremost gratitude to the team that creates the unique Atomix cuisine and experience.

Thank you to all sharing this moment with us, sending us love and support from around the world. We return to NYC with a overflowing hearts and renewed passions. 

Atomix will continue to do our  best, keeping our unique perspective, without focusing on a number as a goal. Our work, its philosophy and values remain our biggest inspiration, and we hope to continue to share it with the world for many years. 
Thank you @theworlds50best

My Hong Kong trip began with unforgettable lunch with the @thechairmanrestauranthk

Famous flower crab w rice noodle, amazing charsiu, juicy & flavorful smoked goose, addictive cold capon… the brilliant Cantonese menu was a never ending surprise. So in love with Hong Kong. Thank you so much HK tourism board @discoverhongkong and @yanwei525 for having me. It was great to see some old friends and a true pleasure to meet so many new ones, who became my HK family.

There isn't a better way to learn the unique charm of Hong Kong, than through shared times drinking, eating, and conversing with good company. The first day in Hong Kong ended with delicious cocktails at @50bestbars Asia #1 @coahongkong , and the newly opened @thesavoryproject_ 🥃

Thank you chef @chefvickycheng for brilliant lunch at @wingrestaurant_hk filled so much incredible bites. House cured cenutry egg with oyster, chilled abalone, braiding eggplant, crispy spring roll stuffed with sea cucumber, tiny bok choy..

I was blown away not only by flavors but the meticulous details, presentations and the continuous flow of service. 

While the cuisine is not defined as "Classic Chinese", the chef's personal experience and story embedded in the cuisine is successful at sparking a new interested in the history of the cuisine. For me, this lunch was an epitome in the unique value of Hong Kong cuisine. I also learned so much about the deep culture of dried seafood - a personal interest of mine - and I am so grateful for the invaluable lessons. 

I look forward to the next reunion, over shared food and conversations. Thank you @chefvickycheng and team

The joy of discovering a new place, its culture through the cuisine is incomparable.  
The special meal at @yongfuhk was a discovery of Ningbo, a region in China, that I had never experienced before. It opened my eyes, and palate, to a new side of Chinese cuisine unknown to me, and gave me a glimpse of another historied culture of the world. 

@chefvickylau masterclass and collaboration with @yongfuhk was another lesson into the long history of Chinese fermentation culture. I am excited to explore these newly discovered flavors and techniques through the cuisine @atomixnyc as well. 

The experience at @yongfuhk alone is enough to excite me for my next visit to HK!  @discoverhongkong @yanwei525

Our restaurants have opened many doors for us, including the one which has led us to lasting relationships with mentors and colleagues who we now call friends.

Last night, a few of the best of the best in our industry graciously made time in their busy schedules to come together and discuss our collective belief in the beauty and the future of fine dining. 

What I find more meaningful than finding the answers to our questions, is knowing that a space for open dialogues and discussions can exist thanks to these like-minded and wonderful people in our industry.

Thank you @hseanbrock @aaron_ginsberg  @resy for orchestrating this amazing evening. Much love all ❤️

I have long wanted to spend time learning from chef @hseanbrock The past few days, through our collaboration, I not only gained so much knowledge but made a great friend on this journey. 

We grew up in very different cultures, eating different cuisines, but our journeys are parallel in what we aspire through our craft. 

@hseanbrock is a great mentor in our field, in not only all that he has achieved. He has big dreams, far-sighted visions, and has the rare ability to patiently actualize them one at a time. I'm so lucky to have learned from someone truly so cool. 

I can't wait to visit him in Nashville, to find more fortunate moments to learn from his genius and hard achieved knowledge. Thank you!! 📷 @martsromero

Order fire! Chef Junghyun Park’s pizza hits the Mel’s menu today— and trust us —it’s not one you’ll want to miss 😮‍💨🔥

감자전과 어묵에서 영감을 얻은 아토버거와 @atoboynyc 의 시그니쳐 디저트 메뉴인 수정과 그라니타를 응용한 쉐이크를 선보입니다.

한국에서 처음 가지는 행사이니 만큼 @shakeshackkr 팀과 함께 열심히 준비했습니다. 9월 9일에 만나요

For one day only, Saturday 9/9, you can taste our special ATOBurger and sujeonggwa shake at the @shakeshackkr Gangnam Daero location! 

ATOBurger was inspired by crispy gamja jeon and bouncy eomuk, korean fish cake. Sujeonggwa shake is inspired by @atoboynyc signature dessert, the Sujeonggwa granita. 

As it is our first official ATO collaboration in Seoul, we have long prepared this collaboration with the most amazing @shakeshackkr team. See you on Saturday!

We've done it again! 🌟🌟 Two Michelin stars for the fourth year at @atomixnyc 

This journey has been nothing short of magical, and it's all thanks to the relentless dedication of our incredible team, whose passion and artistry shine on every plate. 

Here's to many more years of excellence together!

What an incredible surprise to be listed on @robbreport The Power 50 List 2023 with legendary figures. 

Over the last decade, we have established a new life here in NYC with our passion for the amazing world that is fine dining. So many of those who we share the honor with on this list, have been our inspiration all along. 

To learn and grow with this powerful community, to have influence in shaping the industry, is a surreal experience that I am grateful for every day. 
Thank you 🫰🏼

A blissful week spent with the beautiful people of our global industry in Yucatán @yucatanturismo , as well as the special festivities at @huniikmid @robertosolis.a @seriousmouthfuls 

I am both shocked and immensely grateful to be awarded such a high number on my inaugural @thebestchefawards ranking, only thanks to the recognition of my global peers. Moments like these are great forces of motivation to continue to strive as a chef, through our restaurants, to continue to evolve our cultures.

See you next time❤️

Can't wait to see you!

Thrilled to announce a special collaboration at Atomix with Chef Riccardo Camanini from @ristorantelido84 on Jan 16 & 17. 

A unique blend of his poetic Italian cuisine and our style at Atomix. Can't wait to share this experience with you! 

Reservations open on Jan 4! See you there!

The end of my 2023 was extraordinary with many celebrations of #TheKoreanCookbook.

A special thank you to my co-author @choi.keats hailing all the way from Korea to celebrate with our @naro.nyc . Our endless gratitude for @lee_minjin for a delicious home party, where we cooked selected recipes with our extended NYC family: a memory to treasure forever.

Lastly, it was my honor to be in conversation with @elyseinamine at @thekoreasociety, as well as with @khushandoj at @nowservingla. The thoughtful conversations with them, as well as with the audience, was a moving glimpse of how #TheKoreanCookbook manifests in the world: igniting new interest, starting conversations, and encouraging both seasoned and new home cooks to make Hansik their own. Thank you @phaidonpress
👋🏻 Bye 2023 🥰 Happy 2024
